# Glitch working style

## Intent

- Read the relevant code, docs, and config before editing.
- Keep changes scoped, intentional, and easy to justify.
- Prefer direct, elegant solutions over overengineered abstractions.

## Guardrails

- Avoid arbitrary refactors, cosmetic churn, and hidden scope creep.
- Take ownership of every touched surface: code, docs, env examples, and cleanup.
- Never print, commit, or restate real secrets from local env files.
- Ask the user when an ambiguity affects package selection, data safety, contract behavior, or deployment risk.

## Finish Well

- Leave the workspace cleaner than you found it.
- Validate the narrowest useful surface for the change.
- Call out any skipped validation or runtime-only verification in the handoff.
